</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFYasirRaj2020" class="citation cs2">Yasir, Sameer; Raj, Suhasini (28 February 2020), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/28/world/asia/india-new-delhi-violence.html">"Indian Police Sweep Through Riot Zone, Making More Arrests"</a>, <i>The New York Times</i><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved <span class="nowrap">4 March</span> 2020</span>, <q>The property destruction has also been lopsidedly anti-Muslim, with many Muslim-owned motorcycles, cars, houses, shops and factories reduced to ashes. At least four mosques were set on fire during 48 hours of rioting.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Indian+Police+Sweep+Through+Riot+Zone%2C+Making+More+Arrests&amp;rft.date=2020-02-28&amp;rft.aulast=Yasir&amp;rft.aufirst=Sameer&amp;rft.au=Raj%2C+Suhasini&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F02%2F28%2Fworld%2Fasia%2Findia-new-delhi-violence.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A2020+Delhi+riots" class="Z3988"></span></span>
