<li id="cite_note-guardian-3-6-20-3-41"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-guardian-3-6-20-3_41-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFEllis-PetersonAzizur_Rahman2020" class="citation cs2">Ellis-Peterson, Hannah; Azizur Rahman, Shaikh (6 March 2020), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/06/how-can-i-go-back-delhi-fearful-muslims-mourn-riot-dead">"<span class="cs1-kern-left"></span>'I cannot find my father's body': Delhi's fearful Muslims mourn riot dead"</a>, <i>The Guardian</i>, Delhi<span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved <span class="nowrap">7 March</span> 2020</span>, <q>In Shiv Vihar, from where they and many others had escaped, almost every Muslim home lay in blackened ruins, and two mosques looked like bomb sites. For three days, Hindu rioters attacked Shiv Vihar's Muslim localities and ran mayhem without any resistance from police. The mobs repeatedly used gas canisters as weapons, setting them alight and exploding them in Muslim properties so that the walls crumbled entirely.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=%27I+cannot+find+my+father%27s+body%27%3A+Delhi%27s+fearful+Muslims+mourn+riot+dead&amp;rft.date=2020-03-06&amp;rft.aulast=Ellis-Peterson&amp;rft.aufirst=Hannah&amp;rft.au=Azizur+Rahman%2C+Shaikh&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Fmar%2F06%2Fhow-can-i-go-back-delhi-fearful-muslims-mourn-riot-dead&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A2020+Delhi+riots" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-wapo-3-2-20-slater-2-42"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-wapo-3-2-20-slater-2_42-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFSlaterMasih2020" class="citation cs2">Slater, Joanna; Masih, Niha (2 March 2020), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/what-days-of-communal-violence-mean-for-modi-and-for-india/2020/03/01/3d649c18-5a68-11ea-8efd-0f904bdd8057_story.html">"What Delhi's worst communal violence in decades means for Modi's India"</a>, <i>The Washington Post</i><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved <span class="nowrap">15 March</span> 2020</span>, <q>In the riots that swept northeastern Delhi, Muslims mobilized to counter perceived threats and clashed with Hindus. A two-lane road separates Muslim-dominated Mustafabad from Hindu-dominated Bhagirathi Vihar. Hindus say a large mob approached from the Muslim side Tuesday night, throwing stones and Molotov cocktails and firing guns. 'It became difficult to save our lives,' said Yogesh Kumar, 24, an accountant. 'When the fire spreads, everything gets torched,' Sanjay Kumar, 40, said bitterly as he looked around at the destroyed storefronts and burned facades along a lane leading from the main road. He blamed Kapil Mishra, the BJP leader who issued the original threat to protesters who mounted a sit-in.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Washington+Post&amp;rft.atitle=What+Delhi%27s+worst+communal+violence+in+decades+means+for+Modi%27s+India&amp;rft.date=2020-03-02&amp;rft.aulast=Slater&amp;rft.aufirst=Joanna&amp;rft.au=Masih%2C+Niha&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2Fasia_pacific%2Fwhat-days-of-communal-violence-mean-for-modi-and-for-india%2F2020%2F03%2F01%2F3d649c18-5a68-11ea-8efd-0f904bdd8057_story.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A2020+Delhi+riots" clas