</li>
<li id="cite_note-guardian-3-1-20-sikh-hindu-43"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-guardian-3-1-20-sikh-hindu_43-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFEllis-Peterson2020" class="citation cs2">Ellis-Peterson, Hannah (1 March 2020), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/01/india-delhi-after-hindu-mob-riot-religious-hatred-nationalists">"Inside Delhi: beaten, lynched and burnt alive"</a>, <i>The Guardian</i>, Delhi<span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved <span class="nowrap">27 March</span> 2020</span>, <q>But for all the tales of discord, dozens of accounts were also given to the <i>Observer</i> of how Sikh and Hindu families helped save their Muslim neighbours, sheltering them in their homes as the violence broke out or helping them escape as the mobs descended.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=Inside+Delhi%3A+beaten%2C+lynched+and+burnt+alive&amp;rft.date=2020-03-01&amp;rft.aulast=Ellis-Peterson&amp;rft.aufirst=Hannah&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Fmar%2F01%2Findia-delhi-after-hindu-mob-riot-religious-hatred-nationalists&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A2020+Delhi+riots" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Barton2020-44"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Barton2020_44-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Barton2020_44-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFBarton2020" class="citation web cs1">Barton, Naomi (1 March 2020). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://thewire.in/communalism/chand-bagh-delhi-riots-hindu-muslim">"How Muslim and Hindu Neighbours Protected Each Other Through the Long Night at Chand Bagh"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Wire_(India)" title="The Wire (India)">The Wire</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">3 March</span> 2020</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Wire&amp;rft.atitle=How+Muslim+and+Hindu+Neighbours+Protected+Each+Other+Through+the+Long+Night+at+Chand+Bagh&amp;rft.date=2020-03-01&amp;rft.aulast=Barton&amp;rft.aufirst=Naomi&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fchand-bagh-delhi-riots-hindu-muslim&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A2020+Delhi+riots" class="Z3988"></span></span>
