<li id="cite_note-reuters-jain-ahmed-2020-3-16-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-reuters-jain-ahmed-2020-3-16_52-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-reuters-jain-ahmed-2020-3-16_52-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-reuters-jain-ahmed-2020-3-16_52-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFJainAhmed2020" class="citation cs2">Jain, Rupam; Ahmed, Aftab (16 March 2020), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-citizenship-protests-divide-ins/in-indian-capital-riots-deepen-a-hindu-muslim-divide-idUSKBN2130DZ">"In Indian capital, riots deepen a Hindu-Muslim divide"</a>, <i>Reuters</i><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved <span class="nowrap">26 March</span> 2020</span>, <q>But the riots that raged through the district last month appear to have cleaved lasting divisions in the community ...During the day, Hindus and Muslims shun each other in the alleys of the Delhi districts that were hardest hit by the unrest in February. At night, when the threat of violence is greater, they are physically divided by barricades that are removed in the morning.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Reuters&amp;rft.atitle=In+Indian+capital%2C+riots+deepen+a+Hindu-Muslim+divide&amp;rft.date=2020-03-16&amp;rft.aulast=Jain&amp;rft.aufirst=Rupam&amp;rft.au=Ahmed%2C+Aftab&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-india-citizenship-protests-divide-ins%2Fin-indian-capital-riots-deepen-a-hindu-muslim-divide-idUSKBN2130DZ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3A2020+Delhi+riots" class="Z3988"></span></span>
